NIIT-StackRoute 2017-18.
CAP theorem
4
Pick any 2
Consistency
All client see current or latest data regardless
of updates or deletes
Already committed data
Availability
The system continues to operate as expected,
even when one or more node fails
Partition Tolerance
The system continues to operate as expected
despite network or message failure (ability to
communicate with nodes is experiencing
failures)

NIIT-StackRoute 2017-18.
Inserting Data
db.products.insertMany( [
{ item: "large box", qty: 20 },
{ item: "small box", qty: 55 },
{ item: "medium box", qty: 30 },
{ item: large box, qty: 15}
] )
db.products.insertOne(
{ item: "eraser", qty: 25 }
)
NIIT-StackRoute 2017-18.
Updating Data
db.products.updateOne(
{item: large box},
{$set: {qty: 30}
)
db.products.updateMany(
{item: large box},
{$set: {qty: 30}}
)
NIIT-StackRoute 2017-18.
Deleting Data
db.products.deleteOne(
{item: large box}
)
db.products.deleteMany(
{item: large box}
);
NIIT-StackRoute 2017-18.
Querying Data
db.products.findOne(
{item: large box}
)
db.products.find(
{item: large box}
)
NIIT-StackRoute 2017-18.
Aggregating Data
db.products.aggregate(
[{$group: {_id: "$item", MyResult: {$sum: 1}}}]
)
NIIT-StackRoute 2017-18.
Security in MongoDB
Do not run from default port
Authenticate access to DB
Use Role Based Access Control
Do no expose database to outside network or
to cloud
Backup Regularly and Test backedup data

NIIT-StackRoute 2017-18.
Exercise
Create data model for online Blogging app (like Medium)
User registers and blogs
Each blogs gets a unique link to it
Blogs have editable comments & replies
Blogs have tags, votes, shares, citations
Other uses can bookmark blogs
Author is shown details of number reads, views etc., on a date-time scale
Present the data model with the sample data documents and queries
for the same in a Markdown document
Mention what & why exactly you will embed/flatten data and/or not
What indexes you will create
Based on what you will partition the data
